              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "Transport for London (TfL) service updates indicate that the majority of London Underground services are operating normally as of December 2025. However, there are planned closures and service changes affecting various lines:\n\n1. **Northern Line**: Partial closure between Golders Green and Edgware on December 13-14. Replacement bus service NL1 is in operation [Traffic Delays](https://www.trafficdelays.co.uk/london-trains).\n\n2. **Christmas Period**:\n   - No services on the London Underground on Christmas Day.\n   - Boxing Day will have a Sunday service with reduced timetables. No Night Tube or Night Overground services [TfL](https://tfl.gov.uk/status-updates/major-works-and-events).\n   - New Year's Eve will have services running throughout the night, but expect some stations to be closed to manage crowds [London World](https://www.londonworld.com/news/tfl-christmas-travel-schedule-2025-5427070).\n\n3. **Planned Works**:\n   - DLR closure between Bank and Shadwell from December 21 to 30 [Secret London](https://secretldn.com/tfl-christmas-new-year-schedule-disruptions/).\n\nPlease check the TfL website or app for real-time updates and more details on your specific routes.",
